summary:
My passion for success as a financial analyst led me to learn programming a few years ago, despite hating it back as an undergrad. My goal was simple, "make the computer do what the computer's good at, so I can do what humans are good at" - and the only way to do this was programming. After taking some classes in the evenings (C, C#, VBA), enrolling for a year in a Computer Science program, and building skills by doing projects at work, I discovered that I really enjoy programming. This led to discovering data science, and then pursuing a Masters in Data Science at SMU. Now that I've graduated, I'm working in data analytics, and I've never been more excited or passionate about work in my life. 

I moved from the US to the Netherlands in January 2020, and currently living in Amsterdam. I have a Netherlands work visa and do not require sponsorship.
